Practice Areas

Where This Chambers Practises

Each instruction is accepted on the basis of available time, subject-matter suitability, and the ability to provide focused legal attention. This chambers does not accept all work ‚Äî and that is by design.

01

Civil Litigation

Representing parties in suits involving property, contracts, recovery, injunctions, and declaratory reliefs before trial courts and the High Court.

  • Title disputes & property suits
  • Permanent & mandatory injunctions
  • Recovery of money & damages
  • Specific performance of contracts

02

Commercial & Corporate

Legal representation and counsel for businesses navigating disputes, regulatory matters, and contractual conflicts.

  • Commercial Court proceedings
  • Shareholder & partnership disputes
  • NCLT-related litigation
  • Arbitration proceedings

03

Constitutional Matters

Petitions before the Karnataka High Court involving fundamental rights, statutory interpretation, and administrative law.

  • Writ petitions (Art. 226 & 227)
  • Service & employment matters
  • Regulatory & licensing disputes
  • PILs & public interest matters

04

Family & Succession

Handling matters of personal law, matrimonial disputes, inheritance, and succession with discretion and sensitivity.

  • Matrimonial proceedings
  • Probate & Letters of Administration
  • Succession & Hindu law matters
  • Child custody proceedings

05

Labour & Employment

Advising employers and employees on matters arising from service conditions, terminations, and labour court proceedings.

  • Labour Court & Tribunal matters
  • Industrial disputes
  • Employment contract disputes
  • PF, ESIC & statutory compliance

06

Legal Opinions & Advisory

Considered legal opinions for transactions, title due diligence, and risk assessment for individuals and institutions.

  • Property title verification
  • Pre-transaction legal review
  • Demand notice drafting
  • Document & deed review

Profile

Advocate Abhishek Kumar
High Court Advocate

Advocate Abhishek Kumar is a practising advocate enrolled with the Bar Council of Karnataka, appearing before the Karnataka High Court at Bangalore and the Kalaburagi Bench, as well as subordinate courts across the state.

The chambers focuses on quality of representation over volume of instructions. Having appeared in matters spanning commercial disputes, constitutional writ petitions, and civil suits, the practice is structured to provide clear legal strategy from the first consultation through final resolution ‚Äî without unnecessary delay or ambiguity.

Individual clients, family businesses, MSMEs, and larger corporate entities have instructed this chambers for both litigation and advisory work.

How It Works

The Consultation & Engagement Process

01
Initial Enquiry

Submit a brief enquiry via the contact form or telephone. Provide a concise description of your matter and preferred consultation date.

02
Consultation

A structured 45‚Äì60 minute in-person consultation at chambers. Bring all relevant documents. A consultation fee applies.

03
Legal Assessment

After reviewing the facts and documents, a frank assessment of the legal position, likely timeline, and strategy is provided.

04
Engagement

A formal engagement letter is issued confirming fees, scope, and timeline. Proceedings are conducted with regular written updates.

The Approach to Practice

This chambers operates on a considered-instructions model. Every matter is assessed on its merits before acceptance. Clients are provided with an objective view of the strength and weaknesses of their case ‚Äî including a realistic assessment of likely outcomes ‚Äî before any engagement is formalised.

Procedural strategy, evidence management, and case timelines are communicated clearly. Clients are kept informed of every significant development through structured written updates.

This chambers does not advertise success rates, promise outcomes, or guarantee results. Legal proceedings are inherently uncertain. What can be ensured is that your matter receives focused attention, sound preparation, and professional presentation before the court.
